sentences: Margaret Debay Rogers (born April 25, 1994) is an American singer-songwriter and record producer from Easton, Maryland.
She was nominated for a Grammy Award for Best New Artist in 2019.
Maggie Rogers grew up on the Eastern Shore of Maryland along the banks of the Miles River in Easton, Talbot County, Maryland.
Her father is a now-retired Ford Motor Company dealer and her mother, a former nurse, is now an end-of-life doula.
She also spent many summers during her formative years at a rural camp in Maine.
